The Supreme Court on Friday directed the parties in Homa Bay Governor Cyprian Awiti’s petition to return to court on September 3.He is seeking to overturn a Court of Appeal ruling on July 19 that nullified his win. The petition’s verdict will determine whether voters in Homa Bay will have to elect a new governor. The Appeal Court upheld an earlier judgment of the High Court that had established that the IEBC failed to conduct a free and fair poll.  The matter came up for directions on Friday before Supreme Court Deputy Registrar Daniel Keiwua. The registrar directed Awiti and the IEBC to file their submissions and other parties to respond before then. Awiti’s victory had been challenged by his main opponent Oyugi Magwanga. Read: Let’s meet at ballot if you’re man enough, Magwanga tells Awiti Click here for
the latest political news